# Python & FastAPI Conventions

## Path Validation
- Validate `target_path` and `manifest_path` before file access
- Resolve paths within target; reject traversal (`../`)
- Use `Path` and `resolve()` for safe path handling

## FastAPI Routes
- Use `Depends(verify_api_key)` for protected endpoints
- Apply `@limiter.limit()` for rate limiting
- Include `request_id` in log extra for traceability

## Remediation
- Never fabricate fixed versions; use advisory data only
- Mark major upgrades and security-sensitive libs for manual review
- Prefer patch → minor → major upgrade order
